frameDefinitions: A Cognizer calls up an episodic memory of past Experience or an Impression of a Salient_entity formed  on the basis of past experience.
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.

An Initial_element is converted into a Final_element via a process of decay, fusion, or fission which changes the number or type of hadrons (protons or neutrons) in the nucleus of the atoms that make up the Element.  '5.5 percent of nucleii decay from tritium to He3 in a year .'
A Cognizer applies oneself to commit a Pattern to memory, so that the Cognizer would recognize future examples of the Pattern or be able to reproduce it.
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
An Agent has placed a Theme in an accessible but somewhat out of the way Location for the purposes of maintaining it free from harm and illegitimate use while it is not being used.
frameExamples: Kozmo could <t>remember</t> when his modem was the fastest he could buy.
David <t>placed</t> his briefcase on the floor.
5.5 percent of nucleii <t>decay</t> from tritium to He3 in a year .
A gaggle of students were frantically <t>memorizing</t> the answers out in the hall.
In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
listRoleDefinitions: A person who recalls memories of past experience or impressions.
A person or thing that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> remembers as being involved in some state or event or as having some property.
A past event or state that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> witnessed and is now recalling. The <fen>Experience</fen> may be a specific event or state or a vaguer period that is treated as a unit.

A property that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> attributes to the <fen>Salient_entity</fen> based on their past experience of the <fen>Salient_entity</fen> or a category to which the <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is assigned.
A property or role that a <fen>Salient_entity</fen> actually held and which frames the memories that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has of the <fen>Salient_entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> remembers the experience.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
<fen>Time</fen> is when the Placing occurs
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
A substance definable in terms of the kind(s) of atoms that make it up.
The type of <fen>Element</fen> that results from the process.
The type of <fen>Element</fen> that begins the process.
The time at which the <fen>Element</fen> undergoes the transformation.
The location where the nuclear process occurs.
The sentient being that focuses on a <fen>Pattern</fen> so that it will remain in the memory.
The phenomenon that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> observes and commits to memory.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
The location wherein the <fen>Cognizer</fen> memorizes the <fen>Pattern</fen>.
The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who has placed the <fen>Theme</fen> in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that is kept in a <fen>Location</fen> by the <fen>Agent</fen>
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> is kept. Some, though not all, LUs in this frame incorporate this FE.
<fen>Time</fen> is the time period during which the <fen>Theme</fen> is stored.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Storing occurs.
